title: Iron Maiden – Iron Maiden (1980): This is the self-titled debut album from British heavy metal rockers...

attachments.displayName:
Iron Maiden – Iron Maiden (1980): This is the self-titled debut album from British heavy metal rockers Iron Maiden. It’s one of the best debuts from any metal band I can think of from the early 80’s. The musicianship is solid and the band keeps their foot on the accelerator from start to finish. Front-man Paul Di'Anno’s raw, in-your-face, punk-like vocals complement the songs admirably. I cannot think of a better lead singer for the first two Maiden studio albums. With tracks like Sanctuary, Running Free, Phantom of the Opera, Strange World, and Iron Maiden on this album, these guys were destined for “metal” success. Over thirty years and many albums later, they’re still touring, still rocking! So, who’s going to dress up like Eddie the Head (cover art) for Halloween? Cheers!

#IronMaiden #1980 #Metal #HeavyMetal #music #SundayTunes
